    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im doing a lot of hiit lately and my legs feel like they are burning like crazy during the sprints. can u explain what is actually happening with the lactic acid in my muscles when that happens? and how does my body get rid of it after i stop?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That burning sensation during sprints is primarily due to the accumulation of hydrogen ions, which are byproducts of anaerobic respiration when oxygen can't keep up with your high energy demand. While often called \"lactic acid,\" this accumulation is actually what causes the metabolic acidosis and that intense burn. After stopping, your body efficiently removes these ions through several processes, including the Cori cycle in the liver and buffering within the tissues to restore a normal pH balance.",
      "source": "target",
